TITLE: Configuring Number Parsing in XML Parser
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure number parsing options using strnum library with features like handling leading zeros, hex values, and custom number formats.
SOURCE: https://github.com/naturalintelligence/fast-xml-parser/blob/master/docs/v4/2.XMLparseOptions.md#2025-04-19_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const xmlDataStr = `
    <root>
        <a>-0x2f</a>
        <a>006</a>
        <a>6.00</a>
        <a>-01.0E2</a>
        <a>+1212121212</a>
    </root>`;

const options = {
    numberParseOptions: {
        leadingZeros: true,
        hex: true,
        skipLike: /\+[0-9]{10}/,
        // eNotation: false
    }
};
const parser = new XMLParser(options);
const output = parser.parse(xmlDataStr);
```

